cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the performance analysis and optimization of a gradually typed variant of Python, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of static analysis and optimization, which falls under the logic in computer science (cs.LO) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the gradually typed Python program on PyPy, a tracing JIT, which falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
